    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6176: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-21T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 21, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1001. Following information from excellent source believed correct: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Invasion of Greece is planned for early morning October 25. Duce has
                            given the order. Badoglio<note n="29" xml:id="d422fn29">Marshal Pietro
                                Badoglio, Chief of Staff of the Italian Armed Forces.</note>
                            strongly opposed this move on ground that British Fleet will seize bases
                            in Greece from which to bomb oil fields in Rumania. Troops are being
                            embarked at Bari and Brindisi.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>It is reported that four large passenger steamers left Trieste October 18 for
                    Bari and Brindisi and it was inferred by Buffum<note n="30" xml:id="d422fn30"
                        >David H. Buffum, Consul at Trieste.</note> that attack on Greece would
                    begin in near future.</p>
                <pb facs="0555" n="543" xml:id="pg_543"/>
                <p>Inform Navy Department that source of quoted information is Signor “X”.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
